<HEADLINE>
ARMY INSTALLS NEW NIGHTTIME COMBAT TRAINING FACILITY
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  Feb.  16 (CNA) 02/16/07  23:59:06 (By Sofia Wu)
</P>
<P>
The Army Special Service Force training center in central
Taichung County has installed a new nighttime combat training
classroom in the hopes of upgrading the Special Service Force's
nighttime combat capabilities, military sources said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The special training center in Taichung County's Kukuan township
has long been known as a testing ground for the Army's special
service personnel. The new training facility is aimed at honing
the special service forces' nighttime combat skills, sources
said.
</P>
<P>
Noting that intensive, rigorous nighttime combat training is
expected to help special service officers and soldiers overcome
fear and psychological pressures, an Army officer said the
installation is consistent with worldwide security trends.
</P>
<P>
According to the officer, the Army has referred to simialr
foreign facilities in designing the new nighttime training
classroom in which military instructors can design various
training and testing programs to improve team spirit and
coordination.
</P>
